headline: Keysight beats second-quarter estimates on strong demand in its communication business
summary: Keysight, is a provider of electronic design, testing and software products, among other equipment.  The company saw strong sales for its communications equipment from both commercial customers and clients in aerospace, defense and government sectors, with segment sales reaching $913 million, up 9% from last year.

headline: Keysight’s (NYSE:KEYS) Q1 Sales Beat Estimates, Quarterly Revenue Guidance Slightly Exceeds Expectations
summary: Electronic measurement provider Keysight (NYSE:KEYS) reported Q1 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 7.4% year on year to $1.31 billion. Guidance for next quarter’s revenue was better than expected at $1.32 billion at the midpoint, 1.4% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.70 per share was 3.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
